*=====================================================================* * IFSR01 - SrvPgm: IFS-Funktionen * *=====================================================================* * Author : Thomas Raddatz * * Date : 15.03.2004 * * E-mail : thomas.raddatz@Tools400.de * * Homepage: www.tools400.de * *=====================================================================* * * * This software is free software, you can redistribute it and/or * * modify it under the terms of the GNU General Public License (GPL) * * as published by the Free Software Foundation. * * * * See GNU General Public License for details. * * http://www.opensource.org * * http://www.opensource.org/licenses/gpl-license.html * * * *=====================================================================* * History: * * * * Datum Name Änderung * * ---------- ------------ --------------------------------------- * * 01.02.2005 Th.Raddatz Added procedure f_readLineIfsFile() to * * read a line from a streamfile. * * * * 01.02.2005 Th.Raddatz Added procedure f_writeLineIfsFile() to * * write a line to a streamfile. * * * * 15.02.2005 Th.Raddatz Added procedure f_readIfsDir() to * * read a directory. * * * * 03.02.2005 Th.Raddatz Added support for new open() flag * * O_CCSID. * * * * 08.02.2006 Th.Raddatz Changed IFS to be compatible to V5R1. * * * * 24.02.2006 Th.Raddatz Fixed problem that f_readLineIfsFile() * * did not return -1 in case of an error. * * Fixed problem that caller to * * f_readLineIfsFile() could not distinguish* * betwenn EOF and an empty line returned. * * f_readLineIfsFile() now returns -2 in * * case of EOF. * * * * 18.06.2006 Th.Raddatz Fixed problem that caused an endless * * loop in f_renameIfsFile(). * * * * 18.11.2006 Th.Raddatz Added procedure f_getIfsFileCrtTime(). * * * * 17.04.2008 Th.Raddatz Added procedure * * f_getIfsFileDataChgTime(). * * * * 31.08.2008 Th.Raddatz Now correctly producing the target * * file path from the source path * * and the target file name. * * * * 09.09.2008 Th.Raddatz Moved g_hFile and g_path into data * * structure g_handleList. * * Changed f_writeLineIfsFile() to append * * buffer data and end-of-line characters * * to the IFS file at once. (atomic write * * of data and EOL character.) * * * * 18.09.2008 Th.Raddatz Added procedures: f_getIfsTmpPath() * * f_crtIfsDir() * * * * 07.11.2008 Th.Raddatz Added procedures: f_getIfsFileSizeH() * * f_getIfsFileID() * * f_getIfsFileIDH() * * * * 21.01.2009 Th.Raddatz Added procedures: f_getIfsCurDir() * * f_chgIfsCurDir() * * * * 28.01.2009 Th.Raddatz Added procedures: f_dltIfsDir() * * * * 30.01.2009 Th.Raddatz Added procedures: f_isIfsDirEmpty() * * * * 03.02.2009 Th.Raddatz Fixed problem that f_readIfsDir() did * * not properly retrieve the file status * * information (stat()) if a file name * * had trailing blanks. * * * * 18.09.2009 Th.Raddatz Fixed compile problem in IFSTEST_09 * * and added cIFS_RMDIR_DELETE_FILES to * * f_dltIfsDir(). * * * * 20.11.2010 Th.Raddatz Fixed problem that O_CCSID flag was * * not removed from the open flags when * * re-opening a newly created file. * * * * 30.03.2012 Th.Raddatz Added compiler directives to get a clean * * compile on V5R1 systems. * * * * 03.03.2017 Th.Raddatz Added member COPYRIGHT. * * Fixed compile error message RNF7597. * * Updated CEELIB and CLIB. * * * * =================================================================== * * >>PRE-COMPILER<< * * >>CRTCMD<< CRTRPGMOD MODULE(&LI/&OB) + * * SRCFILE(&SL/&SF) SRCMBR(&SM); * * >>COMPILE<< * * >>PARM<< DBGVIEW(*LIST); * * >>PARM<< TRUNCNBR(*NO ); * * >>PARM<< TGTRLS(V6R1M0); * * >>PARM<< OPTION(*EVENTF); * * >>END-COMPILE<< * * >>EXECUTE<< * * >>END-PRE-COMPILER<< * * =================================================================== * H NOMAIN H DEBUG H OPTION(*SRCSTMT : *NODEBUGIO) H DECEDIT('0,') DATEDIT(*DMY.) H DATFMT(*ISO ) TIMFMT(*ISO ) H EXPROPTS(*RESDECPOS) /COPY QIFS,COPYRIGHT * =================================================================== * * *------------------------------------------------------------------------- * Exported functions and type definitions *------------------------------------------------------------------------- /COPY QIFS,PIFS * D ifs_pathV_t S 256A varying based(pDummy) * *------------------------------------------------------------------------- * Private prototypes *------------------------------------------------------------------------- * * Removes a given directory entry from the directory. D lf_removeDirectoryEntry... D PR N D extproc('lf_removeDirectoryEntry') D i_level 10I 0 value D i_directory value like(ifs_path_t ) D i_entry value like(ifs_path_t ) D i_type value like(ifs_type_t ) D i_pUserData * value D o_msg value like(msg_t ) * * Removes a given directory entry from the directory (test mode). D lf_removeDirectoryEntryTestMode... D PR N D extproc('lf_removeDirectoryEntry+ D TestMode') D i_level 10I 0 value D i_directory value like(ifs_path_t ) D i_entry value like(ifs_path_t ) D i_type value like(ifs_type_t ) D i_pUserData * value D o_msg value like(msg_t ) * * Add entry to file handle table D lp_addEntryToFileHandleTable... D PR D i_hFile const like(ifs_hFile_t) D i_path const like(ifs_path_t ) D i_useTmpBuffer N const * * Get path from file handle D lf_getPathFromFileHandleTable... D PR like(ifs_path_t) D i_hFile const like(ifs_hFile_t) * * Returns TRUE if f_writeLineIfsFile() must use a temporary * buffer, else FALSE D lf_useTmpBuffer... D PR N D i_hFile const like(ifs_hFile_t) * * Checks and reallocates size of temporary write buffer. Returns * buffer pointer. D lf_checkAndReallocateTmpBuffer... D PR * D i_hFile const like(ifs_hFile_t) D i_newSize 10I 0 const * * Returns the file handle table index for a given file handle. D lf_getFileHandleTableIndex... D PR 10I 0 D i_hFile const like(ifs_hFile_t) * * Remove entry from file handle D lp_removeEntryFromFileHandleTable... D PR D i_hFile const like(ifs_hFile_t) * * Convert Epoch timestamp to RPG timestamp D lf_cvtEpochTmStmpToRpgTmStmp... D PR Z D i_epochTmStmp 10I 0 value * * Creates a IFS message. D lf_newIfsMsg... D PR likeds(msg_t ) D i_ID const like(msg_t.id ) D options(*omit: *nopass) D i_data 512A const varying D options(*omit: *nopass) D i_type const like(msg_t.type ) D options(*omit: *nopass) * * Checks whether an IFS object is a file; D lf_isFile... D PR N D i_st_stat const likeds(st_stat_t ) * * Checks whether an IFS object is a directory. D lf_isDir... D PR N D i_st_stat const likeds(st_stat_t ) * * Checks whether an IFS object matches a given string pattern. D lf_isEntryEqual... D PR N D i_entry value like(ifs_path_t ) D i_pattern value like(ifs_path_t ) * * Initializes the path structure for the Qp0lGetAttr API. D lf_initializePath... D PR like(ifs_path_t ) D i_path const likeds(Qlg_Path_Name_t) * * Retrieves a file 'time' attribute. D lf_getIfsFileTimeAttr... D PR 10I 0 D i_path const like(ifs_path_t ) D i_attr 10I 0 const D o_time Z * /if not defined(*V5R2M0) D lf_bitand... D PR 10U 0 D i_arg1 10U 0 value D i_arg2 10U 0 value * /endif *------------------------------------------------------------------------- * Global constants *------------------------------------------------------------------------- D cDELIMITER C const(':/\') D cDFT_ASC_CODEPAGE... D C const(850) * D cSLASH C '/' D cBACKSLASH C '\' D cCOLON C ':' * *------------------------------------------------------------------------- * Global fields *------------------------------------------------------------------------- D g_numHandles S 10I 0 inz D g_handleList DS qualified D hFile like(ifs_hFile_t ) inz D dim(100) D useTmpBuffer N inz(cFalse) D dim(%elem(g_handleList.hFile)) D path like(ifs_path_t ) inz D dim(%elem(g_handleList.hFile)) * D g_tempBuffer DS qualified D pData * inz D size 10I 0 inz * D cBUFFER_SIZE C 8196 * *========================================================================= * Checks, whether an IFS directory exists. *========================================================================= * Parameters: * i_path - The name of an IFS directory. * * Returns: * doesExist - Returns TRUE if the directory exists, else FALSE. *========================================================================= P f_isIfsDir... P B export * D f_isIfsDir... D PI N D i_path const like(ifs_path_t ) D o_msg like(msg_t ) D options(*nopass: *omit) * * Return value D doesExist S N inz(cFalse) * * Parameter positions D p_isMsg C const(2) * * Local fields D isPresent S 10I 0 inz D msg DS likeds(msg_t ) inz * * stat() result data structure D st_stat DS likeds(st_stat_t) inz * /COPY QIFS,IFS1011 /COPY QIFS,IFS1015 * --------------------------------------------------------- /free
// If the input path could not be found, ... if stat(%trim(i_path): %addr(st_stat)) = RC_ERROR; // ... then set the error flag doesExist = cFalse; else; // ... else check whether it is a directory or not. if lf_isDir(st_stat); doesExist = cTrue; else; doesExist = cFalse; endif; endif;
// If the directory does not exist, ... if not doesExist; // ... then create message 'directory not found' clear IFS1011; IFS10111 = ''; IFS10112 = %trim(i_path); msg = lf_newIfsMsg('IFS1011': IFS1011); else; // ... then create message 'directory exists' clear IFS1015; IFS10151 = ''; IFS10152 = %trim(i_path); msg = lf_newIfsMsg('IFS1015': IFS1015); endif;
// Set message type to *INFO msg.type = cMsg_Info;
// If the message parameter was passed ... if (%parms >= p_isMsg); // then check if it was omitted CEETSTA(isPresent: p_isMsg: *omit); // If the parameter was not omitted ... if (isPresent = 1); // then pass back the message o_msg = msg; endif; endif;
return doesExist;
/end-free * P f_isIfsDir... P E * *========================================================================= * Checks, whether an IFS file exists. *========================================================================= * Parameters: * i_file - The name of an IFS file. * * Returns: * doesExist - Returns TRUE if the file exists, else FALSE. *========================================================================= P f_isIfsFile... P B export * D f_isIfsFile... D PI N D i_file const like(ifs_path_t ) D o_msg like(msg_t ) D options(*nopass: *omit) * * Return value D doesExist S N inz(cFalse) * * Parameter positions D p_isMsg C const(2) * * Local fields D isPresent S 10I 0 inz D msg DS likeds(msg_t ) inz * * stat() result data structure D st_stat DS likeds(st_stat_t) inz * /COPY QIFS,IFS1012 /COPY QIFS,IFS1013 * --------------------------------------------------------- /free
// If the input file does not exist, ... if stat(%trim(i_file): %addr(st_stat)) = RC_ERROR; // ... then create error message doesExist = cFalse; else; // ... else check whether it is a file or not. if lf_isFile(st_stat); doesExist = cTrue; else; doesExist = cFalse; endif; endif;
// If the file does not exist, ... if not doesExist; // ... then create message 'file not found' clear IFS1012; IFS10121 = ''; IFS10122 = %trim(i_file); msg = lf_newIfsMsg('IFS1012': IFS1012); else; // ... then create message 'file exists' clear IFS1013; IFS10131 = ''; IFS10132 = %trim(i_file); msg = lf_newIfsMsg('IFS1013': IFS1013); endif;
// Set message type to *INFO msg.type = cMsg_Info;
// If the message parameter was passed ... if (%parms >= p_isMsg); // then check if it was omitted CEETSTA(isPresent: p_isMsg: *omit); // If the parameter was not omitted ... if (isPresent = 1); // then pass back the message o_msg = msg; endif; endif;
return doesExist;
/end-free * P f_isIfsFile... P E * *========================================================================= * Fixes a given IFS path name. * (Hint: path = directory + file) *========================================================================= * Parameters: * i_path - A given IFS path name. * * Returns: * path - The fixed IFS path name. *========================================================================= P f_fixIfsPath... P B export * D f_fixIfsPath... D PI like(ifs_path_t ) D i_path const like(ifs_path_t ) * * Return value D path S like(ifs_path_t) inz * --------------------------------------------------------- /free
// Trim input path path = %trim(i_path);
// If no path was specified, ... if path = ''; // ... then return to caller return path; endif;
// Translate backslashes ('\') to slashes ('/') path = %xlate(cBACKSLASH: cSLASH: path);
return path;
/end-free * P f_fixIfsPath... P E * *========================================================================= * Fixes a given IFS directory name. * (Hint: path = directory + file) *========================================================================= * Parameters: * i_dir - A given IFS directory name. * * Returns: * dir - The fixed IFS directory name. *========================================================================= P f_fixIfsDir... P B export * D f_fixIfsDir... D PI like(ifs_path_t ) D i_dir const like(ifs_path_t ) * * Return value D dir S like(ifs_path_t) inz * --------------------------------------------------------- /free
// Trim input directory name dir = %trim(i_dir);
// If no directory was specified, ... if dir = ''; // ... then return to caller return dir; endif;
// Translate backslashes ('\') to slashes ('/') dir = %xlate(cBACKSLASH: cSLASH: dir);
// Append missing slash if %subst(dir: %len(%trimr(dir)): 1) <> cSLASH; dir = %trimr(dir) + cSLASH; endif;
return dir;
/end-free * P f_fixIfsDir... P E * *========================================================================= * Retrieves the file name from a given path name. *========================================================================= * Attention: The f_rtvIfsFileFromPath-function must also be able to * retrieve the file name from pathes starting with 'http://' * or 'ftp://'. Please consider that, when changing the * f_rtvIfsFileFromPath-function. *========================================================================= * Parameters: * i_path - A given IFS path name. * * Returns: * file - The file name portion of the path. *========================================================================= P f_rtvIfsFileFromPath... P B export * D f_rtvIfsFileFromPath... D PI like(ifs_path_t ) D i_path const like(ifs_path_t ) * * Return value D file S like(ifs_path_t) inz * * Local fields D pToken S * inz D token S like(file ) inz * --------------------------------------------------------- /free
// If the path ends with / or \, ... if (f_right(%trimr(i_path): 1) = cSLASH) or (f_right(%trimr(i_path): 1) = cBACKSLASH); // ... then it does not contain a file name file = ''; else; // ... else search for the last token of the path pToken = strtok(i_path: cDELIMITER); dow pToken <> *NULL; token = %str(pToken); pToken = strtok(*NULL: cDELIMITER); enddo;
file = token; endif;
return file;
/end-free * P f_rtvIfsFileFromPath... P E * *========================================================================= * Retrieves the directory name from a given path name. *========================================================================= * Attention: The f_rtvIfsDirFromPath-function must also be able to * retrieve the directory name from pathes starting with 'http://' * or 'ftp://'. Please consider that, when changing the * f_rtvIfsDirFromPath-function. *========================================================================= * Parameters: * i_path - A given IFS path name. * * Returns: * directory - The directory name portion of the path. *========================================================================= P f_rtvIfsDirFromPath... P B export * D f_rtvIfsDirFromPath... D PI like(ifs_path_t ) D i_path const like(ifs_path_t ) * * Return value D directory S like(ifs_path_t) inz * * Local fields D pathLength S 10I 0 inz D dirLength S 10I 0 inz D x S 10I 0 inz D y S 10I 0 inz * --------------------------------------------------------- /free
